The subject includes a systematic comparative description of the English and Russian grammar on the level of word formation, morphology, and syntax. The course provides an overview of the interlanguage differences and universality in the English and Russian languages.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce to students the main typological peculiarities of the Russian and English grammar and to teach students to use theoretical knowledge in the process of teaching Russian as a foreign language, overcoming the interlanguage interference.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the subject a student: 1) knows the main typological differences between the grammar of the Russian and English languages; 2) compares the structure of the Russian language with the one of the students' English language (mother tongue) and explains functional peculiarities of the Russian language; 3) solves methodological and linguistic tasks which are connect with the typological analysis of the Russian and English languages; 4) foresees difficulties in teaching of the Russian language to English-speaking students.
